Below we see a figure about the amount of Corona patients in each state, Washington DC and the American territories*. The X-axis represents the population in millions of the state, and the Y-axis represents the amount of Corona patients in the states and the territories. We see also 10 regions, 7 of them are ‘normal’ regions based on the North, East, South and West. The other three are the regions ‘Alaska’, the ‘Pacific Islands’ and the ‘Atlantic Islands’. To see in which region a state or a territory is located you can scroll in the table below, you can also see the official abbreviation, you will need these to read the figure below.

  • The American territories are Puerto Rico and the American Virgin Islands in the Caribbean, Guam, the Northern Mariana Islands and American Samoa.

When we look at the picture we see all the 56 states or territories and the black line indicates the average of the United States. When a state is above the line, that state has a relative high confirmed cases rate, and when a state is located under the line that state has a relatively low confirmed rate. We see that New York (NY) and New Jersey (NJ) are outliers, they have a very high confirmed cases rate. Florida (FL), Texas (TX) and California (CA) are the opposite, their Corona patient density is very low. Some labels off states are overlapping eachother, the smaller states. In the next figure I’m gonna solve that the labels off the smaller states are overlapping eachother by choosing another scale on the X-axis. The problem is that there are only 4 states with a population bigger or equal to 20 million people. So the right side of the figure has 4 labels and the left side the other 52 labels. The solution is to choose a X-scale that is in a logarithmic scale, a scale where 0 to 1 is the same size as 1 to 10 and 10 to 100. So we make the X-scale logarithmic with base 10 (log10). Instead of an average USA line we use another method to determine the normal states. I the second figure we see a blue line and a grey area around that line, that area indicates the area where a ‘normal’ USA state is located. We see that the outliers are New York (NY), New Jersey (NJ), Illinois (IL), Massachusetts (MA), Connecticut (CT), Louisiana (LA) and Maryland (MD) with a higher confirmed rate than usual. The ouliers when it comes to a lower confirmed rate than usual are Ohio (OH), Montana (MO), the state Washington (WA), North Carolina (NC), Georgia (GA), Florida (FL) and Texas (TX). We see that California is no outlier now, probably because there is no state to compare the population with. When there is no stata to compare the values of California with, the line and area that indicates the normal value is going to California values.
